title: Slow Cooker Shredded Mexican Chicken
directions: Place all ingredients in slow cooker and mix well so all the chicken is coated.
Cook on high for 3-4 hours (or a little moreâ€¦this varies with each slow cooker)
Use a couple of forks to shred the chicken (it will practically fall apart).
Enjoy inside of your tacos or over Mexican rice or as a part of another meal!
ingredients: 2-3 full chicken breasts (I cut them in half so they cook faster)
1 can salsa (I used the basic mild salsa, but you can try any flavor or heat!)
